N2  - The micro politics of labor and management negotiators' boundary role behavior is explored. A negotiator occupies a critical position from which to influence the outcomes of bargaining. A model of collective bargaining is presented that emphasizes the effects on bargaining outcomes of the psychological distances of the negotiators from their respective constituencies.
